DA Gauteng health spokesperson, Jack Bloom on Thursday expressed concern that disruptions continue at the Charlotte Maxeke Johannesburg Hospital, a month after it was violently trashed Bloom said the hospital workers were burning tyres and blocked entrances on Wednesday, causing fear and disruption for patients and staff. “A nurse described to me how she feared for her safety when she couldn’t drive her car out at 1pm because of a burning tyre and aggressive protesters,” said Bloom. “The workers’ grievances are about unpaid performance bonuses and the current wage negotiations.” READ MORE: Nehawu denies reports of strike at Charlotte Maxeke Hospital He said that the Leratong hospital on the West Rand has also been affected by workers who have blockaded the hospital, causing the cancellation of all non-emergency surgeries. Bloom said the Gauteng health department needed to settle worker grievances speedily and fairly, but disruption of hospitals should not be tolerated as they provided an essential service. Meanwhile, the Gauteng Health member of the executive council (MEC) Gwen Ramokgopa was not immediately available for comment. Her office said she had gone to the hospital to try and resolve the matter. – African News Agency